result.execSummary:
The defendant Phillip J Giese was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Determinate sentence: total 3 years (IC 1 year forthwith DCI, eligible for both Challenge Incarceration Program and Substance Abuse Program AMENDED BY COURT 6/27/17 NO JAIL CREDIT ON THIS CASE) (ES-Extended Supervision 2 years)
Concurrent with: with count 4 & CONCURRENT with Oconto Co case 14CF25 BUT CONSECUTIVE to count 53 Marinette Co consolidation case 14CF78

superMiscConds.notes: as agreed to, on all counts including read-ins (Oconto & Marinette Co cases), Joint/Several, court orders total $18,049.95 which includes 5% & 10% restitution surcharges SEE ATTACHED) due while incarcerated & while on ES.
court orders defendant obtain or maintain full time employment or part time employment if enrolled in school.
court orders No contact with any of the victims (Oconto and Marinette Co) or their families and No contact with co-defendants Daemon Hassler, Dustin Elliott, Kyle Davis or Shannon Westphal.

court orders AODA assessment followed by treatment & aftercare, if any portion takes place within a state penal institution, continuation of accepted aftercare treatment upon release to ES.  court orders defendant enter into, participate in & successfully complete any assessments, evaluations and/or treatment programs as directed by DOC.  court orders Absolute sobriety to include No purchase, possession or consumption of any alcohol or controlled substances unless prescribed by physician & then only according to physician's orders, all prescriptions shall be verified by DOC agent.  Defendant is not to be in the company of any person who is using, purchasing or possessing illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.

$278.00 on this case due while incarcerated & while on ES.  court orders DNA sample (but not duplicated).  In addition, on this case, court orders any & all necessary DOC supervision fees due during ES.
